In 2003 an exec by the name of Awesome hit us up to put my songs on his compilation. He ended up taking 4 songs.. 🙏 I’m pretty sure I only got one copy of this CD but I had no idea I also had a vinyl copy. So when I found this the other day I was shocked. But the little blessing there is the fact that @kingreignthe1st had his song “uptight” on the same side of the vinyl that I was occupying. Some real Scarborough vibes from time. 🫡 anyways, the homie @davidclickcox told me he’s seen the man Awesome around. I’ve got quite the funny story about one of our meetings, but I’ll save that gem for a podcast or something. 😂😂 maybe I’ll frame this vinyl tho.. 🤷🏻‍♂️ shit def went “wood in the hood” out here. #history rest peacefully King.. s/o @davinspics for riding with me.. 🫡

*Disclaimer before the golf pundits show up.. 

this was my actual first time ever hitting a driving range to see how I felt about giving this sport a shot. Most of the early ones kept going left.. a lot of them didn’t get any real air or distance. But by this time, I was hitting 200-250 straight with no real idea of what I was doing. What I did realize tho.. I was focused, I was determined, and I was really at peace just trying to do my best. I might go again tonight cause my brother let me hold his set.. the moral of the story, I never thought in a million years I would enjoy just the idea of playing golf. Now I can’t wait to try this again. My brother also says that this video looks like an ad for @theends.ca cause I stand there like some type of Viking on a mountain and shit.. 😂😂 Wear Where You’re From 🔚 

P.S to all my homies that actually golf, I’ll be ready just now fam. Give me a minute. 🏌🏻⛳️

Today marks a significant milestone in our journey together. Four years of love, commitment, and unwavering dedication. Throughout these years, we’ve stood in front of so many challenges, but together, we’ve always found the strength and resilience to overcome them. The bond we share is not only built on love, but also on the unbreakable spirit that comes from weathering storms as a team. Our ability to stand side by side, supporting and uplifting each other, is a testament to the depth of this connection. Together, we’ve conquered mountains, achieved dreams, and created a life & family that is incredible & irreplaceable. While I reflect on the past four years, I feel immense pride in the success we’ve achieved. Here's to many more years of conquering the world together Melly, hand in hand. I love you, and I love every single feather on your wings.. You helped me believe, and I do. ❤️ #familyfirst #october10th 🪽

I’ve learned so many things from my father. Like never giving up, being resilient when the chips are down, and to always find laughter even in the moments least expected. I’ve watched all the odds stack up against him, but you could never get him to fold. He lights up the room when he’s in it. He’s kind to everyone. Most of all, he loves for real. It doesn’t matter what’s in the way cause my pops has no excuses. He’ll get there. When I write the movie, you’ll get a much deeper look into this extraordinary man. But I’m lucky y’all cause he’s my dad. And todays his day. feliz cumpleaños papá I love you so much. 🎈

found an old article from NOW magazine in 2004 when I was the lead in a theatre production of “A Clockwork Orange” at the @harthouseuoft after I did this performance night after night, I developed a serious respect for all theatre actors. It’s tough. If you know anything about ACO, you’ll also know that there was some pretty intense scenes and dialogue in there that really put me to the test. For anyone that was there, you know what I’m talking about. Just wanted to share this awesome memory with y’all.. I’ve never done theatre again, but I would. It was truly a great experience. Rest in peace to our amazing director Robert Ginty. and shout out to my bro @rochesterjuice who was also in the cast with me. He’s got the chops too. 🫡 have a great day everyone. (My Rucker Park #6 jersey is also 🔥🔥🔥🔥 btw)

Hey guys, I have to be honest. While I’m going thru this fight with Cancer, I’m not able to do the things I could usually do to generate my income. Like shows, like studio sessions, being able to run The Ends in a fast way (deliveries went out today) and all of my other revenue streams. It killed me to accept donations cause I know it’s hard for everyone out here. I’m super appreciative and can’t express how much the support has meant to me. So now, thanks to a few good friends, I’m able to do a raffle for a PS5. I’m putting in a couple of sweaters and a bunch of tees. Now if you’ve been on my raffles before, you’ll know I’m very giving and always do more than what I advertise. There will be a lot of chances to win a prize. The grand Prize is a PS5, GTAV, Two hoodies, and 5 Tees! Each ticket is $100 and I believe I’m capping it off at 50 entries. Trust me when I tell you, anyone share this, or participates in this, is REALLY helping me and my family during this time. And I can’t thank you enough 🙏💙 I’ll be doing the draw on Facebook live & on here at the same time. Check my link in Bio to get in on the draw. 🎟️
Follow @theends.ca for me 🔚

First of all, thank you to everyone who participated in that insane ELIMINATOR raffle. Every one of you have contributed to my fight against cancer and I appreciate you all from my heart. “I’m still on an adrenaline rush” is the messages I’m getting from everyone who was watching and in till the end. Congratulations to our first eliminator winner @diana_momma !! 🎉 that was a wild one. So the question that everyone is asking now is.. are we gonna run that back or what?! Let me know in the comments if you’re ready for another crazy prize pack elimination raffle.. again, thank you all. And fuck cancer. 👊😤💙 #TheEnds 🔚 Wear Where You’re From

I wish I had more educational stuff to share but I’m just in that stage where it’s rounds of chemo & recovery until my next scans. The shit is aggressive but I’m doing what needs to be done. I promise I’ll find something to articulate soon. I just need more rest. Hope everyone is blessed & getting screened out there. Don’t be scared. Finding out early is way less scary than finding out late. Trust me. Love y’all. #fuckcancer #teambrigante

aight, so as I mentioned in my stories, I’ve found a passion & distraction for the fight I’m fighting.. I’m now finding & executing all types of recipes from all types of cultures. The other day I made butter chicken from scratch & that was probably my defining moment where I said to myself “this is it, this is what I love to do now.” I salute all the chefs I know that are actually skilled & educated in their craft. For me, I’m just good at paying attention to details and following directions. 😂 I truly wish I could have that type of expertise. But I’m learning. & it’s keeping my mind off of the obvious, while keeping my calories & weight up.. my favourite part of this all tho, is watching my family enjoy each meal as they come. Today, I made a “fajita pasta” & apparently I knocked it out the park with everyone.  So I say all of that to say this. You’re probably gonna see a lot more dish pics in the coming days.. I promise I won’t make it OD but rock with me cause like I said, this is very therapeutic for me right now.. anyways, I hope you all have an incredible holidays with all of your loved ones. May god bless you all & keep you safe. 👨🏻‍🍳 #chefnickolah #foodie

In the early 2000’s, I was a battle rapper from the streets of Scarborough who was kicking ass on stages everywhere I could.. I was still living with my moms and one day I got a random phone call from a man telling me he was shooting a movie and heard I was the guy for a role he needed filled. That man was the legendary  director/writer @carnojoe who went on to make classics like Smoking Aces & The Grey etc. That man put me in the lions den with the great Ray Liotta & Jason Patric to start my career in acting. Well, 20 years later to present time, I get diagnosed with cancer and as an education tool, I decided to go public. I’ve been on a mission to get as much people as I can in the know about colon cancer & how important getting tested is for all of us.. and then I got a phone call. It was Joe again, but this time he says he wants to help me in my fight. Then I got a call from Jason Patric, who also says he’s standing with me in my war. After both calls, I cried to my Melly cause I couldn’t believe these two legends from 20 years ago would offer up such help and support. So here it is. March 22nd, we’ve teamed up with @revuecinema to present a 20 year anniversary screening of NARC, featuring Joe Carnahan, Jason Patric, and yours truly.. with a full Q&A and even possible meet & greets, we will be raising money for my fight as well as giving proceeds to various cancer societies. I will have the link in my bio for you to get the early bird tickets now! I need everyone who truly cares about me to be in the building. This means the world to me. And to Joe & Jason, I love you guys man. True brotherhood stuff right there. See you all soon! #NarcMovie #fuckcancer #march22 #teambrigante #smokingaces [ SHARE THIS POST FOR ME TOO ]
